Description: Sherd of wall with rising handle of Attic pottery cup; burnt; black glazed inside; handle zone reserved outside. Graffito between handle roots.
Curator's comments: Perhaps from a late band-cup; the handles turn up more than in most little-master cups.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1588)
